<h2 id="section-top">Paediatrics services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1063">The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent9b08f958b1654d90b56d2e37ca797dd2">
</div>
<p>The Children and Young People's Unit treats all types of cancer, including  leukaemia, lymphoma, solid tumours, and brain and spinal cord tumours in  children and young people aged 1–24 years. This is done in The Royal Marsden's 31-bed <a href="http://www.royalmarsden.nhs.uk/consultants-teams-wards/treatment-areas/sutton/pages/oak-centre-children-young-people.aspx">Oak  Centre for Children and Young People</a>, one of the largest comprehensive  children and young people’s cancer centres in Europe.</p>
<p>The clinical service is provided by a team of paediatric, clinical and  medical oncologists with on-site access to radiotherapy, diagnostic imaging,  pathology, specialist cancer nursing, symptom care and pharmacy expertise.</p>
<p>Our service includes expert medical and nursing care to ensure the best possible cancer treatment and supportive care. Your diagnosis, treatment and care will be coordinated by two teams of experts (known as a multidisciplinary team or MDT) who work very closely together; one team will manage your medical treatment and care, and the other will manage supportive, social, education, employment and psychological care for you and those close to you. You will be given the name of a member of staff (known as a key worker) who will be your point of contact at the hospital and will help you through diagnosis, treatment and after-care.</p>
<p>We also have Youth Support Worker who coordinates a programme of activities and events so that patients of a similar age can get together. These events have included trips to concerts, recording a song, pamper days, shopping trips to TopShop, outings to restaurants in local areas and bowling.</p>
<p>We also offer a drop-in support group for parents once a month.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>Visiting hours and what you need bring vary in each of the clinical areas. Information about how the hospital works and what you can bring in for each department will be sent to you before your first appointment and offered to you as required.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-serviceteamsummary">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear"><h3><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9662">Staff</a></h3>
<div id="imageContent04371aa87b374ee9bacca3384856d9a9">
</div>
<p>Your care will be jointly coordinated and managed by experts in your cancer type and the teenager and young adult (TYA) team. The team includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Medical consultants experienced in TYA cancer care who will link with other specialists for your cancer type as needed</li>
<li>Consultant in TYA palliative and complex symptom care</li>
<li>Nurse consultant in TYA cancer care</li>
<li>Dietitians</li>
<li>Physiotherapist</li>
<li>Occupational therapist</li>
<li>Psychologists</li>
<li>CLIC Sargent social worker</li>
<li>Teenage Cancer Trust activity coordinator</li>
<li>Speech and language therapist</li>
<li>Clinical nurse specialist in outreach and symptom care</li>
<li>Teacher</li>
<li>Chaplain</li>
</ul>
<p>At The Royal Marsden we have access to a wide pool of high-quality expertise to consult or involve in your cancer care. We are also able to link with services closer to your home.</p>
<p>You, and those important to you, will be involved in your decision-making, planning and care throughout diagnosis, treatment and beyond.</p><p><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9662">Learn more about our staff</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
